HEADWORD: Una boat
<hw>U"na boat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>The English name for a catboat; -- so called because <xex>Una</xex> was the name of the first boat of this kind taken to England.</def>  <rj><au>D. Kemp.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

